label.value: positive regulation of ribosomal protein gene transcription by RNA polymerase II

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the synthesis of RNA from ribosomal protein genes mediated by RNA polymerase II.

label.value: regulation of miRNA-mediated gene silencing

value.value: A process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the downregulation of gene expression through the action of microRNAs (miRNAs).

label.value: negative regulation of miRNA-mediated gene silencing

value.value: A process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of gene silencing by a microRNA (miRNA).

label.value: regulation of gene silencing by regulatory ncRNA

value.value: Any process that regulates the rate, frequency, or extent of gene silencing by RNA. Gene silencing by RNA is the process in which RNA molecules inactivate expression of target genes.

label.value: negative regulation of gene silencing by regulatory ncRNA

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of gene silencing by RNA. Gene silencing by RNA is the process in which RNA molecules inactivate expression of target genes.

label.value: embryonic heart tube dorsal/ventral pattern formation

value.value: The regionalization process in which the areas along the dorsal/ventral axis of the embryonic heart tube are established. This process will determine the patterns of cell differentiation along the axis.

label.value: embryonic heart tube left/right pattern formation

value.value: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of the left/right axis of the embryonic heart tube in space to define an area or volume in which specific patterns of cell differentiation will take place.

label.value: left/right pattern formation

value.value: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of the left/right axis in space to define an area or volume in which specific patterns of cell differentiation will take place or in which cells interpret a specific environment.

label.value: cell migration involved in heart development

value.value: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the progression of the heart over time, from its initial formation, to the mature organ.

label.value: cell migration involved in heart formation

value.value: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that contribute to the formation of the heart. The initial heart structure is made up of mesoderm-derived heart progenitor cells and neural crest-derived cells.

label.value: cardioblast migration to the midline involved in heart field formation

value.value: The orderly movement of a cardioblast toward the midline to form the heart field. A cardioblast is a cardiac precursor cell. It is a cell that has been committed to a cardiac fate, but will undergo more cell division rather than terminally differentiating.

label.value: coronary vasculature development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the blood vessels of the heart over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: coronary vasculature morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of blood vessels of the heart are generated and organized. The blood vessel is the vasculature carrying blood.

label.value: angiogenesis involved in coronary vascular morphogenesis

value.value: Blood vessel formation in the heart when new vessels emerge from the proliferation of pre-existing blood vessels.

label.value: vasculogenesis involved in coronary vascular morphogenesis

value.value: The differentiation of endothelial cells from progenitor cells that contributes to blood vessel development in the heart, and the de novo formation of blood vessels and tubes.

label.value: cell migration involved in coronary vasculogenesis

value.value: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the differentiation of an endothelial cell that will form the blood vessels of the heart.

label.value: cell migration involved in coronary angiogenesis

value.value: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the formation of new blood vessels in the heart from pre-existing blood vessels.

label.value: coronary artery morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of coronary arteries are generated and organized. Coronary arteries are blood vessels that transport blood to the heart muscle.

label.value: epicardium-derived cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell derived from the epicardium acquires specialized features of a cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell. A cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell covers the heart vasculature and lacks transverse striations in its constituent fibers.

label.value: epicardium-derived cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell that was derived from the epicardium over time, from its formation to the mature state.

label.value: epicardium-derived cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell fate commitment

value.value: The commitment of an epicardial cell to a cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell fate and its capacity to differentiate into a cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell.

label.value: endocrine hormone secretion

value.value: The regulated release of a hormone into the circulatory system.

label.value: lipid tube

value.value: A macromolecular complex that contains a tube of lipid surrounded by a protein coat.

label.value: lipid tube assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of macromolecules to form a macromolecular complex that contains a tube of lipid surrounded by a protein coat involved in membrane shaping of vesicle membranes as they fuse or undergo fission.

label.value: lipid tube assembly involved in organelle fusion

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of macromolecules to form a macromolecular complex that contains a tube of lipid surrounded by a protein coat involved in membrane shaping of vesicle membranes as organelles fuse.

label.value: lipid tube assembly involved in organelle fission

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of macromolecules to form a macromolecular complex that contains a tube of lipid surrounded by a protein coat involved in membrane shaping of vesicle membranes as organelles undergo fission.

label.value: response to fungicide

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a fungicide stimulus. Fungicides are chemicals used to kill fungi.

label.value: kidney morphogenesis

value.value: Morphogenesis of a kidney. A kidney is an organ that filters the blood and excretes the end products of body metabolism in the form of urine.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in kidney development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the progression of the kidney over time, from its formation to the mature organ.

label.value: dendritic spine development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label.value: dendritic spine morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label.value: regulation of dendritic spine development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: positive regulation of dendritic spine development

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: negative regulation of dendritic spine development

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label.value: negative regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label.value: positive regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label.value: pattern specification involved in kidney development

value.value: Any developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within the kidney to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate.

label.value: cell differentiation involved in kidney development

value.value: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells of the kidney as it progresses from its formation to the mature state.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in kidney morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation that contributes to the shaping of the kidney.

label.value: hepaticobiliary system process

value.value: An system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of the hepaticobiliary system. The hepaticobiliary system is responsible for metabolic and catabolic processing of small molecules absorbed from the blood or gut, hormones and serum proteins, detoxification, storage of glycogen, triglycerides, metals and lipid soluble vitamins and excretion of bile. Included are the synthesis of albumin, blood coagulation factors, complement, and specific binding proteins.

label.value: hepaticobiliary system development

value.value: The progression of the hepaticobiliary system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The hepaticobiliary system is responsible for metabolic and catabolic processing of small molecules absorbed from the blood or gut, hormones and serum proteins, detoxification, storage of glycogen, triglycerides, metals and lipid soluble vitamins and excretion of bile. Included are the synthesis of albumin, blood coagulation factors, complement, and specific binding proteins.

label.value: common bile duct development

value.value: The progression of the common bile duct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The common bile duct is formed from the joining of the common hepatic duct running from the liver, and the cystic duct running from the gallbladder. The common bile duct transports bile from the liver and gallbladder to the intestine.

label.value: gallbladder development

value.value: The progression of the gallbladder over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The gallbladder is a cavitated organ that stores bile.

label.value: hepatic duct development

value.value: The progression of the hepatic duct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The hepatic duct is the duct that leads from the liver to the common bile duct.

label.value: regulation of mRNA catabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a mRNA catabolic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3',5'-phosphodiester linkage.

label.value: positive regulation of mRNA catabolic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of a mRNA catabolic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3',5'-phosphodiester linkage.

label.value: snRNA import into nucleus

value.value: The directed movement of snRNA, small nuclear ribonucleic acid into the nucleus.

label.value: snRNA localization to Cajal body

value.value: The directed movement of snRNA, small nuclear ribonucleic acid, to a Cajal body.

label.value: hepatoblast differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a hepatoblast. A hepatoblast is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into hepatocytes and cholangiocytes.
